016/11/researching-benjamin-fenn-part-2/","notes":"Blog post with careful analysis; corrects 1630 Mary and John arrival date to likely 1637"},{"short":"Benjamin Fenn Chapter (DAR)","notes":"Chapter named in honor of Benjamin Fenn"}],"marriages":[{"children_ids":["I00008","X00066"],"spouse_id":"X00011","marriage_number":1,"end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1663,"date_year":1638},{"spouse_id":"X00062","children_ids":["I00057","X00106"],"marriage_number":2,"date_year":1664,"date_month":3,"date_day":12}],"death":{"year":1672,"month":9,"day":14,"city":"Milford","state":"Connecticut"},"emigration":{"arrived":"c. 1637","first_residence":"Dorchester, Massachusetts","notes":"Likely arrived 1637 with a group from Buckinghamshire — NOT on the 1630 Mary and John as sometimes stated online. First appears in colonial records 1637; seven-year gap makes 1630 arrival implausible. Removed from Dorchester to Milford where he received lot #3 (2 acres 11 rods 3 poles).","has_discrepancy":true,"discrepancy_note":"Online sources give 1630 / Mary and John. Genealogical blog (Empty Branches) argues compellingly for 1637 Buckinghamshire group. 1637 preferred."},"cross_connections":[{"type":"parallel_descent","related_id":"X00104","display_label":"James Fenn's marriage to Joanna Prudden connected the Fenn-Hooker families.","link_text":"Rev. Peter Prudden"},{"type":"parallel_descent","related_id":"X00103","display_label":"James Fenn's marriage to Joanna Prudden connected the Fenn-Hooker families.","link_text":"Rev. Samuel Prudden"},{"type":"family_connection","related_id":"H00029","display_label":"His daughter Susanna married the Hooker merchant.","link_text":"William Hooker"}],"gender":"male","tags":[],"number_of_marriages":2,"parents":{},"notable":{"is_notable":true,"notable_category":["government"],"notable_blurb":"Milford founder; Connecticut Assistant Governor 1665-1672","primary_url":"https://emptybranchesonthefamilytree.com/2016/11/researching-benjamin-fenn-part-2/","primary_url_la